headline: Indian EV startup Ultraviolette open to licensing battery tech to add revenue stream
summary: BENGALURU (Reuters) -Electric two-wheeler startup Ultraviolette Automotive said on Tuesday it is open to licensing its battery technology, as the Qualcomm and TVS Motor‑backed company seeks to build a new, higher‑margin revenue stream.  Licensing could provide capital to expand manufacturing and the product portfolio, giving companies more financial flexibility, industry experts say.  "A little down the line, we should probably look at other revenue streams from offshoots from the technology side," CEO Narayan Subramaniam told Reuters.

headline: A Fresh Look at Qualcomm (QCOM) Valuation Following New Automotive AI Partnerships
summary: QUALCOMM (QCOM) made headlines recently after announcing a partnership with HARMAN to deliver AI-powered cockpit platforms aimed at transforming the driving experience in Europe and China’s connected vehicle markets. At the same time, the company’s technology is at the heart of Sony Honda Mobility’s new smart electric vehicle project, produced in collaboration with Amazon Web Services.
